The paper deals with the capacity of channels, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The channels considered in the paper involve deletions and states, which are common in communication systems and signal processing, making cs.SI and cs.DS likely categories. The paper also discusses Markov processes, which are a type of stochastic process commonly used in computer science and engineering, making cs.NI a possible category. Finally, the paper uses mathematical techniques to analyze the channels, which could fall under the category of cs.LG (machine learning).
